ncern for difference. This path leads back to the Vectors Lab and its ongoing efforts at the intersection of theory and praxis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aComputer softwarexDevelopment. 0aComputers and women. 0aDigital humanities. 0aScholarly electronic publishing. 0aSoftware engineeringxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060662140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674275287?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674275287423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674275287/original  a978-3-11-060662-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK